- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper mentions the use of machine learning algorithms for segmentation and classification of the mandible, indicating a potential focus on this sub-category. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper may also involve the development of user interfaces or other interactive tools for analyzing and visualizing the mandible data. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia): The use of computed tomography data and potentially other multimedia sources (such as 3D models) could place this paper in the cs.MM sub-category. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper may involve the development of search or retrieval algorithms for finding relevant mandible data or clinical ground truth models.
